### Requirement 13: Sticky Add-to-Cart and Conversion UI Elements

**User Story:** As a customer browsing a product detail page, I want persistent access to the Add-to-Cart button and clear urgency indicators, so that I can act quickly without scrolling.

#### Acceptance Criteria

1. THE Platform SHALL render a sticky bottom bar on the product detail page that becomes visible WHEN the primary Add-to-Cart button is scrolled out of the viewport, containing: product name, price, and Add-to-Cart button.
2. WHEN a product's `stock` field is between 1 and 9 inclusive, THE Platform SHALL display a low-stock indicator reading "Only [N] left in stock!" adjacent to the Add-to-Cart button on both the product card and product detail page.
3. THE Platform SHALL display trust badges (secure payment, free delivery threshold, quality guarantee, easy returns) in a visible section of the product detail page and checkout page.
4. THE Platform SHALL display social proof notifications (e.g., "X people bought this in the last 24 hours") on the product detail page WHERE such data is available from the `sold` field.
5. WHEN a customer is about to leave the checkout page with items in the cart and has not completed purchase, THE Platform SHALL display an exit-intent offer modal once per session offering a time-limited discount code.

